### What problem does this feature solve?
Allow the usage of arrow functions  in copmuted setters
From #7688 

```js
computed: {
  value: {
    get: vm => vm.someValue,
    set: (val, vm) => vm.someValue = val
  }
}
```

### What does the proposed API look like?
```js
computed: {
  value: {
    get: vm => vm.someValue,
    set (val, vm) {
      this === vm // true
    }
  }
}
```

